The paper deals with the problem of rank minimization and its convex relaxation using nuclear norm minimization. This is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.CV are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of an ellipsoidal constraint, which suggests that cs.IT (information theory) and cs.NA (numerical analysis) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides a performance guarantee for the proposed algorithm, which suggests that cs.SI (systems and control) may also be a relevant sub-category.
